Headlines.Headline: Southwestern Energy 1Q Net Down 20% On Higher Expenses

PARAGRAPH.#text: Southwestern Energy Co.'s SWN first-quarter profit declined 20% as operating expenses jumped and natural gas prices slid, although production increased. Meanwhile, a surge in output from unconventional drilling methods have kept a lid on natural gas prices. Average realized price for natural gas slid 24% during the latest quarter. Southwestern posted a profit of $136.6 million, or 39 cents a share, down from $171.8 million, or 49 cents a share, a year earlier.
